The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, June 9: The country?s foreign exchange reserves increased by $1.937 billion to $164.529 billion during the week ended June 2 from $162.592 billion during the week ended May 26. Foreign currency assets increased by $1.23 billion to $156.738 billion during the reporting week, according to figures released by the Reserve Bank. Foreign currency assets in dollars include the effect of revaluation of non-US currencies such as euro, sterling, yen held in reserves.

 Mumbai, June 9: Shareholders of Nicholas Piramal India Ltd have approved the plan to raise $1 billion from the international or domestic markets by issuing foreign currency convertible bonds or other securities.

 Bangalore, June 9: Dena Bank plans to raise an additional capital of at least Rs 250-300 crore by way of hybrid instruments to maintain its capital adequacy ratio at 10.62, said chairman and managing director P.L. Gairola.

 Mumbai, June 9: Ranbaxy Laboratories Ltd has signed a deal with US-based Invagen Pharmaceuticals Inc for marketing zonisamide capsules, used for the treatment of epilepsy, in that country.

 New Delhi, June 9: LG Electronics India plans to invest Rs 900 crore by 2010 at its Pune facility. The company today started operations at its greenfield facility for optical disk drive products in Rajnangaon in Pune.




